| **Server Type**              | **Function**                                                                               |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| ğŸŒ **Web Server**            | Hosts websites and serves web pages (e.g. Apache, Nginx).                                  |
| ğŸ“§ **Mail Server**           | Sends and receives emails (e.g. Microsoft Exchange).                                       |
| ğŸ—„ï¸ **File Server**          | Stores and manages files for multiple users.                                               |
| ğŸ§  **Database Server**       | Stores and handles databases (e.g. MySQL, Oracle).                                         |
| ğŸ› ï¸ **Application Server**   | Runs and delivers software applications (e.g. Tomcat).                                     |
| ğŸ® **Game Server**           | Hosts multiplayer video games.                                                             |
| ğŸ§‘â€ğŸ¤â€ğŸ§‘ **Proxy Server**    | Acts as an intermediary between clients and other servers (used for filtering or privacy). |
| ğŸ” **Authentication Server** | Validates users before giving them access to systems.                                      |

